The '''greater ground robin''' ('''''Amalocichla sclateriana''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Petroicidae]]. It is found in [[New Guinea]].

== Taxonomy and systematics ==
There are two recognised subspecies of the greater ground robin:<ref name=":0">{{Cite journal|last=Boles|first=Walter|date=4 March 2020|title=Greater Ground-Robin (Amalocichla sclateriana)|url=https://birdsoftheworld.org/bow/species/grgrob1/cur/introduction|journal=Birds of the World|language=en}}</ref>

* ''Amalocichla sclateriana  sclateriana'' - The nominate subspecies, found in the mountains of the [[Huon Peninsula]].
* ''Amalocichla sclateriana occidentalis'' - Found in the [[Oranje Mountains]] in central New Guinea. It has browner and more mottled underparts than the nominate subspecies does.<ref name=":0" />{{Sfn|Pratt|Beehler|2014|p=487}}

==Description==
It is the largest robin in New Guinea, at {{convert|20|cm|abbr=on}} in length.{{Sfn|Pratt|Beehler|2014|p=487}}

==Distribution and habitat==
It is endemic to New Guinea. It is found at elevations of {{convert|2500|-|3900|m|abbr=on}}.{{Sfn|Pratt|Beehler|2014|p=487}}

==Behaviour and ecology==

===Diet===
It feeds on invertebrates, such as beetles.{{Sfn|Pratt|Beehler|2014|p=487}}

